# kerning.sdd

Scope: kerning contract for later prototype stages.

## Must

- Start only after base spacing has passed review.
- Prefer class-based kerning once enough glyphs exist.
- Keep kerning exceptions explicit and reviewable.

## Must not

- Begin during the start phase.
- Fix systematic spacing failures with pair exceptions.

## Owns

- Kerning start gate.
- Pair/class distinction.
- Exception review policy.

## Depends on

- `spacing.sdd`
- `../design-principles.sdd`

## Forbids

- Any kerning implementation before approval of the initial skeleton.

## Done when

- Not applicable in start phase. This file is a guardrail placeholder until spacing passes.
